Password Input
- Password is a string masked with "*"
- All attributes are same as textbox.

Syntax:
       <input type="password"  name="password" required  minlength="4" maxlength="14"  placeholder="Password 4 to 14 chars"  pattern="\w{4,14}">


                    Number Input
- It allows input of numeric type values.
- You can limit the number by using
    a) min
    b) max
    c) step

Syntax:
 <input type="number" name="rate" min="10.45" max="18.45" value="10.45" step="0.01">


                  Range Input
- It is similar to number input.
- It comprises of a slider to select value.
- It uses min, max and step.

Syntax:
 <input type="range"  name="rate" min="10.45" max="18.45" step="0.01" value="10.45">

                 Color Input
- It shows a color picker.
- It allows to select a color.
- It uses 6 chars hexadecimal code.

Syntax:
 <input type="color"  name="color" value="#ff00ff">

                Email Input
- It is similar to textbox with attributes.
- It validates email format.
- It will not allow normal string format. It must have "@" in string.

Syntax:
 <input type="email"  name="email"  required  placeholder="Your email address">


URL Input
- It validates URL.
- URL must have protocol and domain.

    www.amazon.in        // invalid
    https://www.amazon.in    // valid

Syntax:
 <input type="url" name="URL"  placeholder="Your website address" required>

                 Date & Time Input
- HTML provides various types for data and time values.
    a) date
    b) time
    c) datetime-local
    d) week
    e) month
    f)  year [obsolete]
    g) datetime [obsolete]
- You can't select a range of dates.
- You can restrict the date range by using "min" and "max" attributes.
- Date format is always  "year-month-day" for developer.

Syntax:
  <input type="date" min="2024-11-01"  max="2024-11-18">
  <input type="month">
  <input type="datetime-local">
  <input type="week">
